\begin_layout Section
Ramsey Taxation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The goal of this homework is to study optimal taxation.
 You will derive some results known as the Atkinson-Stiglitz results on optimal taxes.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Households.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consider the following static economy.
 Household are endowed with one unit of labor 
\begin_inset Formula $n=1$
\end_inset

 which earns a wage 
\begin_inset Formula $w$
\end_inset

.
 They maximize a CES utility over 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 goods,
 indexed by 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

.
 To purchase their goods,
 they sell their labor.
 They face the following problem:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{U}=\max_{\left\{ c_{i}\right\} }\sum_{i=1}^{N}\left(\omega_{i}^{1-\rho}c_{i}^{\rho}\right)^{\frac{1}{\rho}}
\]

\end_inset

subject to:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sum_{i=1}^{N}\left(1+\tau_{i}\right)p_{i}c_{i}=w.
\]

\end_inset

The difference here relative to what we've seen in the past is the presence of a sales tax 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau_{i}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Question #1.
 Solve for the household's optimal expenditures given the vector of prices 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Government.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The government purchases 
\begin_inset Formula $N^{g}$
\end_inset

 goods,
 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{i}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $i\in\left\{ 1,2,...,N^{g}\right\} $
\end_inset

 which we stack in the vector 
