.
 These goods are bought competitively at prices 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}^{g}$
\end_inset

.
 The government faces the following budget constraint:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sum_{i=1}^{N^{g}}p_{i}^{g}G_{i}=\sum_{i=1}^{N}\tau_{i}p_{i}c_{i}.
\]

\end_inset

In other words,
 the government pays for its own goods by collecting taxes.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Firms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The economy features a single firm with production technology:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{H}\left(\boldsymbol{y,g}\right)=n
\]

\end_inset

where:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{\mathcal{H}}=\left(\sum_{i=1}^{N}\eta_{i}^{1-\psi}y_{i}^{\psi}+\sum_{i=1}^{N^{g}}\gamma_{i}^{1-\psi}g_{i}^{\psi}\right)^{\frac{1}{\psi}}.
\]

\end_inset

Relative to what you've seen in the past,
 here the firm sales consumer goods,
 
